<!DOCTYPE html> <!--[if lt IE 7]><html lang="en" class="ie ie6 lte9 lte8 lte7"> <![endif]--> <!--[if IE 7]><html lang="en" class="ie ie7 lte9 lte8 lte7"> <![endif]--> <!--[if IE 8]><html lang="en" class="ie ie8 lte9 lte8"> <![endif]--> <!--[if IE 9]><html lang="en" class="ie ie9 lte9"> <![endif]--> <!--[if !IE]><!--><html lang="en"> <!--<![endif]--><head profile="http://gmpg.org/xfn/11"><title>Go Easy on Yourself, a New Wave of Research Urges - NYTimes.com</title><meta charset="UTF-8"><script src="http://typeface.nytimes.com/xaz5nrm.js"></script><script>try{Typekit.load();}catch(e){}</script><link rel="stylesheet" href="http://css.nyt.com/css/0.1/screen/build/blogs/well/styles.css?v=07-19-2012" media="screen"> <!--[if IE]><link rel="stylesheet" href="http://css.nyt.com/css/blogs/3.1/screen/themes/universal/ie.css" media="screen"> <![endif]--> <!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="http://html5shiv.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js"></script><![endif]--><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><meta name="keywords" content="Anxiety and Stress,Diet and Nutrition,Mental Health and Disorders,Weight" /><meta name="description" content="A new area of psychological research suggests that self-compassion, a measure of how kindly people view themselves, may be the first step toward better health. &lt;a href=&quot;http://well.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/02/28/go-easy-on-yourself-a-new-wave-of-research-urges/&quot;&gt;Read&amp;#160;more...&lt;/a&gt;" /><meta name="des" content="Anxiety and Stress;Diet and Nutrition;Mental Health and Disorders;Weight"><meta property="og:title" content="Go Easy on Yourself, a New Wave of Research Urges" /><meta property="og:type" content="article" /><meta property="og:url" content="http://well.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/02/28/go-easy-on-yourself-a-new-wave-of-research-urges/" /><meta property="og:site_name" content="Well" /><meta property="og:description" content="A new area of psychological research suggests that self-compassion, a me